The Herald Nyore Madzianike Senior Court Reporter The trial of former Cabinet Minister Prisca Mupfumira and former National Social Security Authority (NSSA) director Banabas Matongera in which they allegedly ordered the construction of low-income houses in Gweru through a local company, Drawcard Enterprise without board approval and going to tender opened today at the Harare Magistrates Court. Mupfumira and Matongera denied the charges when they appeared before Harare regional magistrate Mr Ngoni Nduna.